    "summary": "In my 26 years in Medical Devices I have gained experience in various areas of device development. From academic research and feasibility studies to development of Class III implantables and evaluation of the complete technical dossier in clinical evaluation.\n\nI am an analytical thinker, pragmatic researcher and empathic leader.\n\nI would like to apply my clinical and R&D skills in a medical device start-up/scale-up (or company with similar culture), preferably as a hands-on team lead, helping your company getting your device to market.\n\nKey skills: \n* Working with patients and medical professionals to identify opportunities for improvement of clinical practice and evaluate solutions (#designthinking).\n* Translating ideas from literature or the lab to products that add clinical value.\n* Creating a safe environment with open communication and trust. In my experience people perform at their best when they can also connect to teammates on a personal level (#psychologicalsafety)\n* Coaching people in creating rules and procedures that work for them.\n* Discover patterns in data/signals and use it to create algorithms that are accurate and easy to understand. The simplest solutions are easiest to define, implement, validate and maintain.\n* Create regulatory strategies. When to move from research and discovery (outside QMS) to design and development under a QMS. It is easier to cut corners if you understand the consequences.\ud83d\ude42",
